      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera features the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant, delivering 315 hp through a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The engine benefits from VarioCam Plus timing, ensuring a broad torque curve and high-revving linear power delivery. This example has been fastidiously maintained, including the critical LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a recent rear main seal replacement. The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing MacPherson struts up front and a multi-link rear setup for legendary feedback. Finished in Arctic Silver over black leather, the exterior shows honest patina consistent with its mileage, while the interior remains a driver-focused cockpit. It is a mechanically sound, turn-key enthusiast machine ready for the canyons.",
